# SEO Optimization Best Practices

## Context

- Optimize landing page for search engines
- Improve discoverability and rankings
- Implement proper metadata and structured data
- Ensure fast page loads and mobile-friendly design

## Requirements

### Metadata (Next.js App Router)

- Export metadata object from layout.tsx or page.tsx
- Include title, description, keywords, and Open Graph tags
- Use generateMetadata for dynamic metadata
- Implement canonical URLs
- Add robots meta tags
- Include Twitter Card metadata

### Structured Data (JSON-LD)

- Implement JSON-LD structured data for rich snippets
- Use Schema.org vocabulary
- Include Organization, WebSite, and WebPage schemas
- Add Article schema for blog posts (if applicable)
- Include BreadcrumbList for navigation

### Technical SEO

- Implement sitemap.xml generation
- Create robots.txt file
- Ensure proper URL structure (clean, descriptive)
- Implement 301 redirects for moved content
- Use HTTPS everywhere
- Optimize page load speed (Core Web Vitals)
- Ensure mobile responsiveness

### Content Optimization

- Use semantic HTML structure
- Implement proper heading hierarchy (h1-h6)
- Include alt text for all images
- Use descriptive link text (avoid "click here")
- Optimize content for target keywords
- Ensure content is accessible and readable

### Performance for SEO

- Optimize images (WebP, lazy loading)
- Minimize JavaScript bundle size
- Implement code splitting
- Use CDN for static assets
- Enable compression (gzip/brotli)
- Minimize render-blocking resources

